creator: Mary Hannay Foott
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 17 recordings of Where the Pelican Builds by Mary Hannay Foott. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for June 1, 2014. Read in English by Angela J Brett; Assaf Koss; Arup Sen; David Lawrence; Ernst Pattynama; Ezwa; fshort; Glenn O'Brien; Jason Mills; Jeanie; Jannie Meisberger; Julia Niedermaier; Leonard Wilson; Malcolm Fisher; SkyAlbatross; Tom R Wilson and Teresa Bauman. Mary Hannay Foott was an Australian poet and editor who is best remembered for this Fortnightly poem - Where the pelican builds. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (12MB)
